Description: Fragment of oal handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharp turn. Clay fine brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp with grape cluster symbol and Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 182, 3 Name Doros An unpublished stamp from Delos is from the same die, as Tanais 95/2709.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1065)
